OL,3,CWater quality of two bathing spots
OL,4,Cmarked as 'too poor' for swimming
OL,6,FThe water quality of two Cumbrian
OL,7,Fswimming spots have been marked as
OL,8,F'too poor' for bathing, an Environment
OL,9,FAgency review concludes.
OL,11,F450 areas, which are regularly used by
OL,12,Fswimmers, have been tested in the
OL,13,FEnglish coastal and inland bathing
OL,14,Fwaters review by the Environment
OL,15,FAgency.
OL,17,F92% of bathing waters in England have
OL,18,Fmet minimum water quality standards in
OL,19,Fannual figures released on 26 November
OL,20,F2024, which is a 4% drop on last
OL,21,Fyear's results.
