OL,3,CWater quality of two bathing spots
OL,4,Cmarked as 'too poor' for swimming
OL,6,FAlan Lovell, Environment Agency Chair,
OL,7,Fsays there is a "growing public
OL,8,Fdemand" for more bathing sites to be
OL,9,Ftested across the country.
OL,11,FHe said: "While overall bathing water
OL,12,Fquality has improved in recent decades
OL,13,Fdue to targeted investment and robust
OL,14,Fregulation, today's results show there
OL,15,Fis much work still to do, particularly
OL,16,Fto bring our inland bathing waters up
OL,17,Fto standard.
