OL,6,F"We are working with the water
OL,7,Findustry, farmers and local
OL,8,Fauthorities and are investing in our
OL,9,Fregulation, with more people on the
OL,10,Fground, updated digital assets and new
OL,11,Flegal powers to improve our bathing
OL,12,Fwaters for all."
OL,14,FThirty-seven bathing waters in England
OL,15,Fwere classed as 'poor' in this year's
OL,16,Freview. Emma Hardy, Water Minister,
OL,17,Fsays the figures show that 'too many
OL,18,Fswimming spots are polluted'.
